    <item>
      <title>Episode 142: LiveView 1.0 Deep Dive</title>
      <link>https://elixirpodcast.example.com/episodes/142</link>
      <description>We sit down with Chris McCord to discuss the LiveView 1.0 release, what changed, and what the future holds.</description>
      <pubDate>Thu, 06 Jun 2024 05:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <enclosure url="https://cdn.elixirpodcast.example.com/episodes/ep142-liveview-deep-dive.mp3" length="67108864" type="audio/mpeg"/>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">ep142-liveview-1-0</guid>
      <itunes:title>LiveView 1.0 Deep Dive</itunes:title>
      <itunes:episode>142</itunes:episode>
      <itunes:season>5</itunes:season>
      <itunes:duration>01:12:45</itunes:duration>
      <itunes:explicit>false</itunes:explicit>
      <itunes:episodeType>full</itunes:episodeType>
      <itunes:image href="https://elixirpodcast.example.com/episodes/ep142-artwork.jpg"/>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In this episode, we sit down with Chris McCord to discuss the long-awaited LiveView 1.0 release.</p>
<h2>Topics Covered</h2>
<ul>
<li>The journey from 0.x to 1.0</li>
<li>Breaking changes and migration path</li>
<li>New features: streams, async assigns</li>
<li>Performance improvements</li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>
